<h1 align="center">Connector Design</h1>
<h2 align="justify">Principal objective of Component Based Development </h2>
<ul>
  <li>
<h3><font style="font-weight: 400">Rapid development of software products from a 
kit of components.</font></h3>
  </li>
  <li>
<h3><font style="font-weight: 400">Change the functionality of an assembled 
product just by reconfiguring its components.<br>
&nbsp;</font></h3>
  </li>
</ul>
<h2>The Usual Approach</h2>
<ul>
  <li>
<font color=red>
<h3> <span style="font-weight: 400">An Interface specifies list of operations a 
Component performs.</span></h3>
</font>
  </li>
  <li>
<h3> <span style="font-weight: 400">Little attention paid to interaction that 
must exist over time between components.</span><span style="font-size: 14pt; font-weight: 400"><br>
&nbsp;</span></h3>
  </li>
</ul>
<h2>Connector Based Approach</h2>
<ul>
  <li>
<font color=red>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400">Uses Connectors to model the 
interactions. A Connector is an abstract representation of the 
interaction between the components it connects. </span></h3>
</font>
  </li>
  <li>
<h3><span style="font-weight: 400">Powerful technique for Designing Component 
Infrastructures <br>
with replaceable parts.</span></h3>
  </li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>

